\subsection{Agree to disagree?}
\fr{\ft{Agree to disagree?}

  \begin{itemize}
  \item players predict the probability of some event
  \item players start with the same prior
  \item players then get private information through their information function
  \item can it be common knowledge that players assign different probabilitites to the event?
  \item No!
  \item intuitive story:
    \begin{itemize}
    \item each player sees other players' predictions and can revise
      own prediction
    \item if other players' prediction is different from yours, they
      have some information you do not have
    \item $\Ra$ Bayesian updating $\Ra$ revise prediction
    \item repeat infinitely\dots
    \item eventually everyone should have same prediction
    \end{itemize}

  \end{itemize}


