\begin{prop}
  The electronic mail game has a unique Nash equilibrium in which both players always choose $A$.
\end{prop}
\textbf{Proof. }The proof is by induction.\\
\begin{enumerate}
\item In state $(0,0)$ P1 chooses \dots % the dominant strategy $A$.
\item If P2 does not receive any message, he plays \dots
